item.title: Darla add a quote by Madeleine L'Engle
item.description: "They are very young. And on their earth, as they call it, they never communicate with other planets. They revolve about all alone in space." "Oh," the thin beast said. "Aren't they lonely?" -- Madeleine L'Engle

item.title: Darla add a quote by Barbara Kingsolver
item.description: "I felt emptied-out and singing with echoes, unrecognizable to myself: that particular feeling like your own house on the day you move out." -- Barbara Kingsolver

item.title: Darla add a quote by Tom Stoppard
item.description: "We cross our bridges when we come to them and burn them behind us, with nothing to show for our progress except a memory of the smell of smoke, and a presumption that once our eyes watered." -- Tom Stoppard
